    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered for the discerning collector is a meticulously preserved 2002 BMW M3 (E46). This example features the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing system for surgical throttle response. Power is delivered through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a variable M differential lock. The chassis is structurally sound, with proactive rear subframe reinforcement and fresh bushings throughout. The factory Laguna Seca Blue finish remains in concourse condition, complemented by a pristine interior. This vehicle has undergone a comprehensive mechanical inspection, ensuring the high-revving 8,000 RPM redline is met with absolute reliability. A rare, turn-key opportunity to own a peak-era analog driver's car.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
